# Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in the values for development.

For production, set these in Vercel environment variables.

## Frontend (.env or .env.local)

```
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3001
```

For production deployment on Vercel, set:
```
VITE_API_URL=https://your-backend-url.railway.app
```

## Backend (.env)

Copy from `.env.example` in the backend folder:

```
PORT=3001
NODE_ENV=development
CORS_ORIGIN=http://localhost:5173,http://localhost:5174
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://amylenoir:PASSWORD@lenoirport.ihj9e1t.mongodb.net/portfolio-cms?retryWrites=true&w=majority
JWT_SECRET=your-secret-key
ADMIN_PASSWORD=admin123
```

For production (Railway):
```
PORT=3000
NODE_ENV=production
CORS_ORIGIN=https://your-domain.vercel.app,https://amylenoir.com
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://amylenoir:PASSWORD@lenoirport.ihj9e1t.mongodb.net/portfolio-cms?retryWrites=true&w=majority
JWT_SECRET=use-a-strong-random-string
ADMIN_PASSWORD=use-a-strong-password
```
